950
01:54:06.251 --> 01:54:08.126
You should do too.

951
01:54:09.417 --> 01:54:12.917
Maybe then you'd hear
how often you keep interrupting me.


952
01:54:24.584 --> 01:54:27.209
You haven't changed a bit.

953
01:54:37.209 --> 01:54:44.167
So let's say I fire up my computer

954
01:54:46.209 --> 01:54:50.959
to order a tuned-up
version of Alicia Silverstone...


955
01:55:14.917 --> 01:55:16.792
- Good evening.
- Good evening.


956
01:55:16.959 --> 01:55:20.542
Dad will be right up, he's talking
with some woman downstairs.


957
01:55:20.709 --> 01:55:22.834
- I'll just have a Coke.
- Of course.


958
01:55:25.209 --> 01:55:30.251
Kindly throw away the cup
when you're done, please.


959
01:55:34.167 --> 01:55:36.959
What do you kids
call trash cans these days?


960
01:55:38.042 --> 01:55:40.251
<i>Creme de la creme...</i>

961
01:55:42.334 --> 01:55:44.292
- Toilet.
- What?


962
01:55:45.917 --> 01:55:48.251
Sorry, my hearing aid is acting up.

963
01:55:50.084 --> 01:55:52.709
It's strange. The battery's brand new.

964
01:56:00.834 --> 01:56:03.042
What's taking them so long?

965
01:56:10.626 --> 01:56:13.542
Could you go get your father?

966
01:56:15.251 --> 01:56:18.792
You'll end up in the garbage chute
tomorrow after physio.


967
01:56:20.792 --> 01:56:24.542
I don't have time to wait.

968
01:56:26.126 --> 01:56:28.917
It's not that early anymore...

969
01:56:44.417 --> 01:56:45.959
Listen...

970
01:57:59.501 --> 01:58:03.251
THE LAST FAMILY